# Strategy notes and internal AI workflow artifacts — same category as the
# decision docs above. STRATEGY_NOTES captures the reasoning behind
# architectural choices (including what was rejected and why);
# STRATEGY_CHAT_SEED is the prompt used to ground new internal strategy
# conversations. Both are useful to maintain across sessions but contain
# internal meta-commentary that doesn't belong in the public repo.
docs/STRATEGY_NOTES.md
docs/STRATEGY_CHAT_SEED.md

# Backlog tracked locally until items migrate to GitHub Issues. The
# current BACKLOG.md contains pre-issue planning notes, phase-specific
# follow-ups, and implementation details that will eventually be split
# into proper Issues with labels, milestones, and assignees. Keeping it
# private during this transition avoids exposing half-formed items.
docs/BACKLOG.md

# Deployment-specific verification scripts — these run Observibot against
# a live monitored system and produce deployment-specific output, so they
# stay local and are not part of the generic OSS surface.
scripts/live_verify_chat.py
scripts/verify_db.py

# Claude Code harness state (local session settings, scheduled task locks).
.claude/

# Sprint reports and external-review syntheses — same category as the
# REVIEW_SYNTHESIS docs above. These contain LLM-reviewer feedback,
# implementation notes, and live-dashboard screenshots from the operator's
# own deployment, so they stay local.
docs/REPORTS/
